    <item>
      <title>Maximising the results-to-effort ratio</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/maximising-the-results-to-effort-ratio/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 29 Jul 2014 08:20:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/en/maximising-the-results-to-effort-ratio/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/writing-guide/zh/maximising-the-results-to-effort-ratio.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/maximising-the-results-to-effort-ratio/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/maximising-the-results-to-effort-ratio/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/advice-on-writing-papers/maximising-the-results-to-effort-ratio/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;maximising-the-results-to-effort-ratio&#34;&gt;Maximising the results-to-effort ratio&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;[Reprinted from a Google Buzz post of Feb 12, 2010; expanded, July 20, 2019.]&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As a professional courtesy, research papers in mathematics should be at a &amp;ldquo;local maximum&amp;rdquo; with respect to the results-to-effort ratio: any &amp;ldquo;cheap&amp;rdquo; consequences, generalisations, variants, illustrative counterexamples, etc. of one&amp;rsquo;s main results should be put into the paper if this can be done with only moderate effort on the author&amp;rsquo;s part. If one is too lazy to do this, these consequences might not appear in the literature for some time (as they are too close to your own paper to be separately publishable in their own right), and each reader may have to rederive them by himself or herself, which is a much less efficient process in the long run.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Think ahead</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/think-ahead/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 18:58:01 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/think-ahead/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/think-ahead.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/think-ahead/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/think-ahead/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/think-ahead/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;think-ahead&#34;&gt;Think ahead&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Worse than being blind, is to see and have no vision.&#xA;— Helen Keller&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It is really easy to get bogged down in the details of some work and not recall the purpose of what one is actually doing; thus it is good to pause every now and then and recall &lt;strong&gt;why&lt;/strong&gt; one is pursuing a particular goal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
